==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: pectin
<hw>pec"tin</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧k"t⟦icr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>phkto`s</grk> curdled, congealed, from <grk>phgny`nai</grk> to make
fast or stiff: cf. F. <ets>pectine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>One of a series of carbohydrates, commonly called
<altname>vegetable jelly</altname>, found very widely distributed in the
vegetable kingdom, especially in ripe fleshy fruits, as apples,
cranberries, etc. It is extracted as variously colored, translucent
substances, which are soluble in hot water but become viscous on
cooling. It is commonly used in making fruit jelllies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pectinal</ent>⟦br⟧
